programme.title: Monster Iowa Buck Returns, Summer Trail Cam Tips For Deer Season Success
programme.desc: In this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, Josh Sparks heads out on some newly acquired permission ground to begin the plan for a successful season. In the meantime, Owen Reigler discusses the drought conditions that have been facing Iowa and the issues that come with that as well as some trail camera strategies you can use during this time. Kaleb Greiner is back to work on the plan for GQ Jr. as the deer has been very frequent on the Cuddeback cameras. In the process, Kaleb goes over his strategies for summer trail camera placement and how it helps him come hunting season. Finally, the Midwest Whitetail team has some awesome news as we welcome Drake Lamb back to the team. We're super excited and we hope everyone enjoys the video. Thanks for the support!

programme.title: Chasing A Giant Droptine Buck In Iowa, Choosing The Best Tree Stand Locations
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we kick things off by joining Josh Sparks as he discusses a few of the key things he looks for when picking tree stand locations on a brand new piece of property. Then following that, we jump to Kaleb Greiner who does a deep dive on how he plans to approach hunting the farm that he spent so much time on last season. With it being year two, Kaleb talks about what he learned last season, how it is influencing stand locations for this fall, and how he hopes it will help Steve catch up to the giant drop tine buck that's been showing up on camera. Finally, we jump over to Area 52 with Zach Rozmus who sets the stage for two new stand locations for this coming fall.

programme.title: 3 Killer Spots For A Giant Buck, Bow Hunting Adjustments Based On Past Success
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we kick things off with Lee Abraham in southern Iowa as he breaks down his plan for his top target buck, a giant known as GQ Jr. Looking back on the historic chase that saw him wrap his tag on a giant 204" buck known as GQ, Lee breaks down what he's learned from those hunts and makes adjustments for this season. Those adjustments come in the form of 3 different killer stand locations that he hopes will find him wrapping a tag around another giant this season. Following this, we jump over to catch up with Andy Melton and David Williams who give us an update on their '23 deer season plans and a brief how-to on growing your own oak trees at home! Finally, we jump to the west to the plains of Kansas with Mike Reed who gives us a sneak peek at what's to come in next week's show. Stick around and catch an awesome property that could be yours listed by our partners at UC Hunting Properties.

programme.title: Setting A Killer Stand For Bowhunting, Drake's New Plan For His Top Target Buck
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we start off in Eastern Iowa with Kaleb Greiner for his raw reaction to his first card pull of the season. After setting up a Cuddeback camera back in July hoping to find back a familiar buck, he comes to find that the Iowa monarch has returned sporting his best rack to date. After that, we get an update from Drake Lamb in Southern Iowa on his game plan for the fall and the projects he has completed throughout the summer on a small permission farm he calls "The 50." A familiar foe has returned to the farm and Drake is all in on preparing for battle with "Sticks."

programme.title: Finding Back The Biggest Buck Owen's Ever Hunted, Experimental Fall Plots
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we kick things off by joining Owen Reigler down in southern Iowa. All off-season and summer, Owen has been putting in the time trying to make the spots he hunts better. Both for hunting and for the wildlife overall. First, he dives into a new change in his plan to find back what could be the biggest buck he's ever hunted. Then the guys jump to the new 80 where Owen updates two spots that have been completely transformed since the project started. Finally, Owen gets a first look at how the food plot on the newest permission farm is doing. Following all of this, next we jump to Eastern Iowa with Rye Ludwig who tries an experimental technique to growing two new fall plots. As always, we appreciate you taking the time to watch the episode!
